<seg id="849">According to the wording of Law No. 235 / 2004, which applies from 1 January 2005, the place of performance for the supply of electrical energy is the place of performance at which the purchaser has his legal registered office, registered office or permanent establishment for which this delivery takes place.</seg>
<seg id="850">Therefore, the Czech tax obligations should not have indicated the electricity supplies in their ZM for 2005.</seg>
<seg id="851">The fact that both taxpayers treated the supply of electrical energy in their ZM as intra-Community supplies led to a difference of CZK 503,881,939 in MIAS.</seg>
<seg id="852">Concluding remark</seg>
<seg id="853">Through the cooperation, the goals of the BRH and the NKò were achieved.</seg>
<seg id="854">Both courts of auditors gained in-depth knowledge of the VAT administration systems in the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="855">The cooperation revealed differences in the two systems and in the legal regulations relevant to VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="856">During the parallel tests, interesting cases of intra-community deliveries or acquisitions came to light.</seg>
<seg id="857">Some of them are worth further observation.</seg>
<seg id="858">On the basis of the audit results, both courts of auditors drew up recommendations on the management of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="859">The follow-up of these recommendations in the form of a control review should be part of the further observation.</seg>
<seg id="860">The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of the two Court of Auditors is the basis for the successful implementation of future audits in the field of VAT administration.</seg>
<seg id="861">Communiqué</seg>
<seg id="862">This report was written in Czech, English and German and signed by the President of the Supreme Control Office of the Czech Republic and the President of the Federal Court of Auditors of the Federal Republic of Germany.</seg>
</p>
